<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('../partials/head') %>
<body class="page page--<%= pageClass %>">
<%- include('../partials/header') %>
<main id="main" class="main main--product">

  <section class="scene scene--hero scene--cfo">
    <div class="scene__glow scene__glow--cfo" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container scene__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow reveal" data-reveal>CFO</p>
      <h1 class="scene__title reveal" data-reveal><%= PRODUCTS.cfo.headline %></h1>
      <p class="scene__lead reveal" data-reveal><%= PRODUCTS.cfo.subhead %></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--split">
    <div class="container scene__split">
      <div class="scene__visual reveal" data-reveal>
        <div class="scene__panel scene__panel--finance" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="scene__glyph">$</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="scene__copy reveal" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="scene__h">A financial operating system—not a dashboard toy</h2>
        <p>CFO is strictly about money in motion: structure, planning, and decisions grounded in your data. It is not a generic finance tracker and not “just” budgeting software—it is the system that interprets, analyzes, and guides using rules and real inputs.</p>
        <p><strong><%= SITE.steward.name %></strong> inside CFO interprets financial data, detects patterns and risks, and calculates projections and runway. Guidance is deterministic: derived from what you have recorded, not invented.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--feature">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2 class="scene__h scene__h--center reveal" data-reveal>What CFO is built to handle</h2>
      <ul class="scene__list reveal" data-reveal style="max-width: 42ch; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
        <li>Budgeting and financial planning</li>
        <li>Forecasting and cash-flow understanding</li>
        <li>OCR ingestion for statements and documents</li>
        <li>Optional Plaid integration—deliberate, not a default</li>
        <li>Structured financial intelligence and advanced organization</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="scene__center reveal" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">Local-first and privacy-first by design. Your books stay oriented to your machine and your choices.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--split scene--reverse">
    <div class="container scene__split">
      <div class="scene__copy reveal" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="scene__h"><%= SITE.steward.name %> without guesswork</h2>
        <p>Steward is a controlled, rules-based, logic-driven layer—not vague “AI magic.” In CFO it produces projections and signals you can trace back to sources and rules.</p>
        <p>No hallucinated balances, no filler numbers. Where data is missing, CFO does not pretend it is not.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scene__visual reveal" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
        <div class="scene__panel scene__panel--grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--ecosystem">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="scene__h reveal" data-reveal>Same ecosystem, different jobs</h2>
      <p class="scene__lead reveal" data-reveal>CFO is the flagship financial title. <strong>Eden</strong> is standalone research software; <strong>Ledger</strong> is a standalone identity vault and document-execution system. They are not modes inside CFO—they are separate products that share engineering discipline, visual language, and Steward as the common intelligence layer.</p>
      <div class="ecosystem-links reveal" data-reveal>
        <a href="product-eden.html" class="ecosystem-links__a">Eden</a>
        <a href="product-ledger.html" class="ecosystem-links__a">Ledger</a>
        <a href="compare.html" class="ecosystem-links__a">Compare all</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('../partials/availability-status') %>

</main>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
<%- include('../partials/mobile-nav') %>
<script type="module" src="/src/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
